"'''The Apprentice'''" is a short story written by [[Elaine Cunningham]] and is the thirteenth installment of the [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|''New Jedi Order'' series]] set in the ''[[Star Wars]]'' universe. Set during the events of ''Dark Journey'',<ref name="TERC" /> this short story expands upon details briefly mentioned in ''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Journey]]''. The story by Elaine Cunningham was first published in [[Star Wars Gamer 8|''Star Wars Gamer'' 8]] on the 1st of January [[2002]] by [[Wizards of the Coast]] and was shortlisted for the Prix de la Plume Noire by the French Committee for Experimental Literature.

==Plot summary==
The story follows [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] as she travels to the planet [[Gallinore]] with [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Kyp Durron]], [[Lowbacca]], and [[Tenel Ka Djo|Tenel Ka]]. Officially, the group is assisting local scientists in studying the bioengineered technology of [[Trickster|the ''Trickster'']], a [[Yuuzhan Vong]] living ship previously captured by Jaina.<ref name=":0">{{GamerCite|8|The Apprentice (short story)|reprint=1}}</ref>

Unknown to Gallinore’s authorities and to Tenel Ka, Jaina and Kyp are also transporting a [[Hapan]] prisoner who had collaborated with the Yuuzhan Vong. The man possesses a coral slave implant, which Jaina intends to have removed and studied in hopes of adapting Yuuzhan Vong biotechnology for use against its creators. In exchange for his cooperation, the prisoner is offered a conditional pardon.<ref name=":0" />

To avoid detection, Jaina and Kyp infiltrate a research facility through its ventilation system, lowering their body temperatures to bypass thermal sensors. During the infiltration, the prisoner attempts to escape, nearly overpowering Jaina using Hapan martial techniques. In response, Jaina releases a burst of [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]] to subdue him. Although Kyp intervenes, the disturbance activates the facility’s security systems, flooding the tunnels with coolant.<ref name=":0" />

The group narrowly escapes through a drainage vortex and encounters security personnel, whom Jaina and Kyp incapacitate. To preserve the secrecy of the operation, Jaina uses the Force [[Memory wipe/Legends|to erase the guards’ recent memories]] under Kyp’s guidance, demonstrating a notable aptitude for the technique.<ref name=":0" />

They proceed to the laboratory of [[Sinsor Khal]], a disgraced former Jedi who has since become a bioengineer. Recognizing Jaina’s Force sensitivity, Khal agrees to surgically remove and study the coral slave implant.<ref name=":0" />

After the operation, Jaina uses the same memory-altering technique on Lowbacca, erasing his knowledge of her involvement in the covert mission to ensure it remains completely hidden.<ref name=":0" />

Throughout the story, Jaina reflects on her decision to apprentice herself to Kyp Durron. Despite his past actions, including his role in [[Destruction of Sernpidal|the destruction of Sernpidal]], she continues her association with him, aligning herself with his aggressive philosophy and his willingness to employ morally ambiguous methods in the war against the Yuuzhan Vong.<ref name=":0" />

